                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/105.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Edwards</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juarez</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 22, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s February 21. Request for the body of William Benton was made by me
                    during interview of the evening of nineteenth. Villa said he could not let the
                    body go now but would do so later. He was then requested as a favor to me to
                    mark well the grave. This he promised to have done. Will make another attempt to
                    secure the body.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
